<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1920,2017]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1956,1981]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Notes.</emphasis>
This oligolectic species is known from neighbouring states. It is included based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell's" box="[1239,1436,1956,1981]" firstAuthor="Mitchell's" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 538" refId="ref96571" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1960) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume I. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 141, 1 - 538." type="book chapter" year="1960">Mitchellâ€™s (1960)</bibRefCitation>
authority and records from the Chicago area within 
<quantity box="[748,835,1992,2017]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
west of the southwest corner of 
<collectingRegion box="[1214,1322,1992,2017]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Michigan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LaBerge" firstAuthor="LaBerge" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 143" refId="ref92617" refString="LaBerge, W. E. (1977) A revision of the bees of the genus Andrena of the Western Hemisphere. Part VIII. Subgenera Thysandrena, Dasyandrena, Psammandrena, Rhacandrena, Euandrena, Oxyandrena. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 103, 1 - 143." type="journal article" year="1977">LaBerge 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pearson" box="[222,379,152,176]" firstAuthor="Pearson" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="373 - 441" refId="ref98804" refString="Pearson, J. F. W. (1933) Studies on the ecological relations of bees in the Chicago region. Ecological Monographs, 3, 373 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1943111" type="journal article" year="1933">Pearson 1933</bibRefCitation>
). It visits 
<taxonomicName box="[490,720,151,176]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polemoniaceae" genus="Polemonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptens">
<emphasis box="[490,720,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Polemonium reptens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., which is restricted to the southern corners of 
<collectingRegion box="[1278,1388,151,176]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Michigan</collectingRegion>
, but also 
<taxonomicName box="[204,450,188,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Geranium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculatum">
<emphasis box="[204,450,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Geranium maculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName authority="Michx." authorityName="Michx." box="[540,865,188,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis box="[540,773,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ranunculus hispidus</emphasis>
Michx.
</taxonomicName>
, which are more widespread in the LP (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref100883" refString="Robertson, C. (1929) Flowers and insects: Lists of visitors of four hundred and fifty-three flowers. The Science Press Printing Company, Lancastre, Pennsylvania, 221 pp." type="book" year="1929">Robertson 1929</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Voss &amp; Reznicek" box="[221,482,223,248]" firstAuthor="Voss" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref105324" refString="Voss, E. G. &amp; Reznicek, A. A. (2012) Field manual of Michigan flora. University of Michigan Press, Ann Arbor, Michigan, 990 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.3998 / mpub. 345399" type="book" year="2012">Voss &amp; Reznicek 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
